    <h1>Green&#xAD;land loses chunk of glacier larger than Paris</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200916/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-09-16"><time>2020-09-16</time></a>
        - <span>FRONT PAGE</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>As the sum­mer melt sea­son reaches its peak, the largest Arc­tic ice shelf in Green­land has jet­ti­soned a mas­sive</p>
    <p>113 sq km chunk of ice that is larger than Paris. The three satel­lite images here show the Spalte Glacier in Au­gust 2018 (far left), Septem­ber last year (cen­tre) and last month.</p>
    <p>A huge chunk of ice roughly as large as the catch­ment area for Sin­ga­pore’s Ma­rina Reser­voir, or one-sixth of the coun­try ’s land size, has bro­ken off from the Arc­tic’s largest re­main­ing ice shelf due to rapid cli­mate change</p>

